  abstract = {Neutral hydrogen (H i) has been detected in the Local Group dwarf spheroidal galaxy Sculptor with the 64 m Parkes single-dish telescope and mapped with the Australia Telescope synthesis array. Most of the detected H i is in two clouds \textasciitilde 15'-20' away from the optical center. The gas is observed at the same systemic velocity as the stars, but at {$>$}=125 km s\textasciicircum -1 away from the Magellanic Stream components in that region. A lower limit to the H i mass of 3.0 x 10\textasciicircum 4 M\_{$\odot$} is derived from the synthesis observation for an (M\_H I/L\_B) \textasciitilde = 0.02. This amount of H i is compatible with mass loss expected from normal giants, even if only 10\% of the gas is retained by the galaxy in its neutral form.},
