  abstract = {We use the proper motions (PM) of half a million red giant stars in the Large Magellanic Cloud measured by Gaia to construct a 2D kinematic map of mean PM and its dispersion across the galaxy, out to 7~kpc from its centre. We then explore a range of dynamical models and measure the rotation curve, mean azimuthal velocity, velocity dispersion profiles, and the orientation of the galaxy. We find that the circular velocity reaches {$\sim$}90~km\,s-1 at 5~kpc, and that the velocity dispersion ranges from {$\sim$}30--40~km\,s-1 in the galaxy centre to {$\sim$}15--20~km\,s-1 at 7~kpc.},
